The paper deals with the theoretical model of a version control system, which involves the manipulation of files and patches. This falls under the realm of programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the category theory behind the model, which could be classified under logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with collaboration and coordination between distant collaborators, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and concurrency (cs.CC).
